content.description:
Nice balancy face climbing on side pulls and pockets.

The route shares the first bolt with When I Was A Young Boy and then goes up right.
content.location: To the right of When I was a young boy and jesse has homework

climbs.name: When I Was A Young Boy I Had Me A Beer

content.description: Tricky Face Climbing.
content.protection: Just to the right of Jesse has Homework
content.location: 3 Bolts to anchor of Jesse has Homework

content.description:
In honor to the German Soccer Team of 2014 and their victory in the Fifa World Cup. Start on small boulder at the base and move up on small side pulls, crimps and long reaches. Very sustained and on from the first move. Stick Clip the First Bolt is recommended.

THIS IS A PROPOSED GRADE!
content.location: Dark Side West, just to the left of the Bavarian Bratwurst Massacre.

content.description: Start on a little block at the base of the route and  then delicately move up the face to a big move at the end.
content.protection: 3 Bolts to 2 Bolt Anchor. Stick clipping the first bolt is recommended but not required. The 3rd clip is fairly hard and a attentive belay is mandatory.
content.location: This route is to the left of Family Business.

content.description: 8 bolts to long chains
content.location:
To the left of

New Slang

(5.13).

content.description: Climb big moves with big holds up ledge to jugs at the top.
content.location:
To the right of

In Orbit

(5.10).

climbs.name: Scarface And A Fist Full Of Cocaine

content.description: This route is basically a 3 move boulder problem into 5.8 climbing. Start on an undercling and a sharp crimp and make your way up, having somewhere above your head a limestone pebble. One bolt to the anchor of jesse has homework.
content.protection: 1 Bolt to 2 Bolt Anchor. The first bolt is high, but the difficult part is right of the ground and with a spotter or a crashpad it is totally safe to climb.
content.location: This route is immediately to the left of Jesse Has Homework.

content.description: Crimpy pulling on small flakes.
content.location: To the left of A Tiger Dancing

content.description:
Named my left cheek and climbed on TR with a grade of 11c. After holds broke never climbed again neither on TR nor Lead according to the old topo.

Cryptic Beta and still some loose stuff on it.
content.location: To the left of Ten Percent Professional

content.description: Really fun route with a roof and jugs at the top
content.protection: 5 bolts to chain and rap hanger
content.location:
to the right of

Fear of Wild Places

(5.10).

content.description: Climb the Route In Orbit, but instead of moving right into small steps, go straight through the roof  on surprisingly good holds. Do the final one arm hang chalk up, before clipping the anchor
content.protection: 5 Bolts. 3 From In Orbit, then 2 new silver bolts to a 2 bolt chained anchor.
content.location: To the right of the Neg. Creep Direct

content.description: short fun crack/seam climbing. good warm up. still needs a bit of cleaning, but fun lybacking.
content.location: Walk left of "Small steps" 20' or so. Obvious crack/seam. fun for beginners first lead well protected.

content.description: Climb the first 3 bolts of "The Neg. Creep Direct". At the 3rd bolt, break out left to a side pull which leads to a good horizontal crack with perfect handjams. From there, clip a new bolt (black painted bolt) and continue straight up on good holds. Above the bolt, there is a 2 bolt ring anchor waiting (also painted black)
content.location: Same start as Neg. Creep Direct

content.description: 6 bolts to anchor. Start left of large cave and is hard climbing all the way up.
content.location: Starts just left of the cave in the middle.

content.description: You have to go left to get the 5.12 rating.  Although there is a bolt missing at the top, making for a scary topout.  If you go right on bolts it makes the rating 5.10.  This route starts with really cool underclinging up to harder moves.
content.protection: 7 quickdraws, be careful of the topout with out the bolt.
content.location: a prominent right leaning crack on the right side of the wall

content.description: Find the good holds to pull up over the roof
content.location:
Located to the right of the cave and

All the Kings Horses

(5.12).

content.description: good holds lead to a half mantle crux move then up to crimps to the top. Cool shelf holds and big feet. a fun warm up
content.location: to find this route, from the darkside moving furthest right to left: from "small steps" and "in orbit" move left along the wall. Move 10ft past a bolted seam/crack and your there.

content.description: This route is very fun with cruxes coming low (getting off the ground) and a balancy move at the top.  A really enjoyable route!
content.location:
To the right of

Negative Creep Direct

(5.12).

content.description:
Dedicated to a local Laramie climber, who was stuck in Budapest in the summer of 2014.

This route has the same start as Small Steps. Clip the first bolt of Small steps before moving right (follow the black bolts) towards an obvious black arete. The climbing involves crisps pockets and some foot work.
content.location: On the far right side of the Dark Side. Start on Small Steps.

content.description: Crimpy boulder start to sustained but easier top part.
content.location: To the right of Ovulation Station. Start on the big jug flake

content.description: This route is marked as the Blue Prints Project in Davin Bagdonas guide book (Route #9) Climb through a roof and up the thin slap to eventually good pockets
content.location: To the left of Chris can't fly

content.description: Climb through cool huecos to a weird crack
content.location: to the right of love life

content.description: Start on obvious flake and move up on techy and sustained face climbing. Move left on the second bolt and up through the bulge to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: Look for Obvious Flake at the start and black bolts. The 3rd bolted line to the left of Bavarian Bratwurst.

content.description: Start below the rood and pull up into the crack. A really fund climb!
content.protection: 1 bolt low, and then either gear or toprope
content.location: the prominent crack above the cave on the right

content.description: Start on an obvious, lay away on pockets and move over to some interesting moves in pockets. The start is marked by a black fixe bolt.
content.location: Obvious Arete to the left of "The Negative Creep"

content.description: Climb up the straight bolt line on the aret. Goes together with the normal Bavarian at the second bolt. Do a V7/8 Boulder into a 12c finish. The start has been done without any cheater stones!!!

Start on a jug rail and traverse right on big moves. Join Good Bye Lenin and finish it off. Pumpy athletic movements to techy balance face with a big hard move on it. Single moves might not be harder then 12c, but being very sustained 13a seems reasonable.
content.location: To the left of Good Bye Lenin!

content.description: Climb over a roof and go up a thin face.
content.location:
To the right of

Chris Can't Fly

(5.10c).

content.description: 6 bolts to a fixed ring anchor. Start on a small pedestal and traverse right on good incut edges then climb through an undercling and straight up.
content.location: Furthest left route on the wall.
